<h5><strong>Qualifications for Living in Single Student On-Campus Housing</strong></h5>
<p><strong><br /></strong></p>
<p>Any student who can live in Approved Housing can live in On-Campus Student Housing. Those who qualify to live in approved housing are:</p>
<p><br />1.	Students who are currently attending BYU-Idaho as a student admitted to a track (the technical term is that a student must be a matriculated student).</p>
<p><br />2.	Students who are off-track and continue to live in the immediate Rexburg area (includes summer session).</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr />
<h3>For more information on <a href="x9331.xml">who can and cannot live in Approved Housing, click here</a>.</h3>
